quran[32]{c,v,t}:
  25,21,"And those who fear not the meeting with Usl say: wherefore are not angels sent down unto us or wherefore we see not our Lord! Assuredly they have proven stiff-necked in their souls and have exceeded the bounds with excess great"
  25,22,"The Day whereon they shall behold the angels on that day there will be nea joy for the culprits, and they will say: away! away"
  25,23,"And We shall set upon that which they worked, and shall make it as dust wind-scattered"
  25,24,Fellows of the Garden shall be on that Day in a goodly abode and a gocdly re pose
  25,25,And on the Day whereon the heaven shall be rent asunderg from the q clouds and the angelhall be sent downll with a great descending
  25,26,"The dominion on that Day rhall is; be the true dominion, of the Compassionate, l and it shall be anday upon the infidels hard"
  25,27,"On the Day when the wrong-doer shall gnaw his hands saying: would that had taken with the apostle a way"
  25,28,Ah! woe unto me! wouldthat had never taken such a one for a friend
  25,29,Assuredly he misled me from the admonition after it had come unto ine. Verily the Satan is ever unto man a betrayer
  25,30,"And the Apostle will say: my lord! verily my people too k this Qur'an as a thing to be shunned"
  25,31,And even scals We appointed unto every prophet an enemy from among the culprits. And thine Lord sufficeth as GUide and Helper
  25,32,"And those who disbelieve say: wherefore is the Qur'an not revealed unto him entire at once! Thus---We reveal- that We may establish thy heart there with; and We have repeated it with a repetition"
  25,33,And they come not unto thee with a similitude but We bring thee the truth and an excellent interpretation
  25,34,They who shall be gathered prone on their faces unto Hell-- those shall be worst in respect of place and the most astray in respect of path
  25,35,And assuredly We vouchsafed unto Musa the Book and We placed with him his brother Harun as a minister
  25,36,"Then We said: go ye twain unto a people who have belied Our signs. Then We annihilated them an utter annihilation"
  25,37,"And the people of Nuh! When they belied the apostles We drowned them, and made them a sign unto mankind. And We have gotten ready unto the wrong-doers a torment afflictive"
  25,38,And the 'Aad and the Thamud and the dwellers of the pass and generations in-between many
  25,39,And unto each! We propounded similitude thereunto; and each We ruined an utter ruin
  25,40,And assuredly they have gone by the township whereon was rained the evil rain. Are they not wont to see it? Aye! they expect not Resurrection
  25,41,"And when they behold thee, they hold thee up for mockery: is this the one whom Allah hath sent as an apostle"
  25,42,"Well nigh he had led us astray from our gods if we had not persevered towards them. Presently they shall know, When they behold the torment, who, more astray in respect of path"
  25,43,Hast thou observed him who hath taken as his god his own desire! wilt thou be over him a trustee
  25,44,"Or deemest thou that most of them hear or understand? They are but like unto the cattle; nay, they are even farther astray from the path"
  25,45,Hast thou not observed thine lord-how He hath stretched out the shadow? And if He had willed He would have made it still. Then We have made the sun for it an indication
  25,46,Then We draw it toward Us with an easy drawing
  25,47,"And it is He who hath made for you the night a covering, and the sleep; repose, and hath made the day a resurrection"
  25,48,And it is He who sendeth fort the winds as a herald before His mercy and We send down from the heaven water pure
  25,49,"That We may quicken thereby a dead land, and We give drink thereof to that which We have created of cattle and human beings many"
  25,50,"And We set it forth among them, that they may be admonished, but most men begrudge aught save infidelity"
  25,51,"And if We had willed, We would have raised up in each town a warner"
  25,52,"Se obey not thou the infidels, but strive against them therewith with a great striving"